DataElement.preferredName: Product Infusion Procedure Administered Begin Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The month, day, and year the product (e.g.,human drugs; therapeutic biologics; allergenics; cells, tissue and gene therapy products; blood components and blood derivative products)  infusion procedure began.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A thing produced by or resulting from a process. EXAMPLE(S): drug, device. The FDA list of regulated products: animal and human drugs; therapeutic biologics; allergenics; cell, tissue and gene therapy products; blood components; blood derivative products; devices; and animal (pets and livestock) and human food/feed (medicated and un-medicated); cosmetics; pet treats; and dietary supplements._A method of putting fluids, including drugs, into the bloodstream. Also called intravenous infusion._The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).
